## API Endpoints

- `GET /api/sightings` returns the merged sightings dataset used by the map
- `POST /api/report` creates a new report in SQLite
- `GET /api/species-stats` returns aggregated species statistics

### Example payload

```json
{
  "date": "2025-01-20",
  "city": "London",
  "environment": "Park",
  "host": "Dog",
  "species": "Marsh tick",
  "latinName": "Ixodes apronophorus",
  "severity": "low",
  "notes": "Found near a tree",
  "email": "example@gmail.com"
}
```

## Run Locally

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Open the app at `http://localhost:5000`.

## Why this project stands out

- Focused on a real public-health problem
- Clear separation between data, API, and UI
- Uses live data plus a fallback to stay reliable
- Presents the project in a way that is easy to demo in an interview

